<DOC><DOCNO> AP890604-0024 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-04-89 1209EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--IvoryBan     06-04 0078</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Ivory Ban,0080</SECOND><HEAD>France Bans Ivory Imports</HEAD><DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   France is banning imports of ivory to help saveAfrican elephants, the government announced Sunday.   Brice Lalonde, the environment minister, said the importprohibition will take effect Monday.   Experts estimate that the African elephant population hasdwindled to half a million under pressure from poachers who killelephants for their tusks.   France currently imports $3 million worth of ivory annually,most of it processed in Hong Kong.</TEXT></DOC>